General Hanover led a full life of integrity, proven leadership and selfless-service. My team and I worked with members of the community to properly honor General Hanover after his passing in 2017. We found it fitting to name the facility for the unit which he formerly commanded.

Today, the U.S. Army Reserve Center in Bryan was officially named after one of America’s heroes from the Greatest Generation and one of the Brazos Valley’s finest leaders – Brigadier General Joe G.
